<p><tags><tag kind="heading2">## </tag></tags>Search — and Find</p>
<p></p>
<p>So many texts, so many words? In case you lose track, Ulysses offers a number of search options.</p>
<p></p>
<p>Group search is available at the top of the sheet list and can be restricted to certain text elements, such as headings or comments. In the editor, Find and Find &amp; Replace are also at your disposal.</p>
<p></p>
<p><tags><tag kind="heading3">### </tag></tags>Quick Open</p>
<p></p>
<p>The fastest way to get to work is Quick Open. Try this:</p>
<p></p>
<p><tags><tag kind="unorderedList">- </tag></tags>Hit <element kind="code" startTag="`">⌘O</element> to open the Quick Open panel.</p>
<p><tags><tag kind="unorderedList">- </tag></tags>Enter a search term to scan the current section of your library, e.g. enter “Quick”.</p>
<p><tags><tag kind="unorderedList">- </tag></tags>Click to get back here.</p>
